post_text:
The Reading Marching Blue Devils are pleased to announce the addition of color guard to our performance this fall!

We are looking for students in grades 8-12 to participate in this wonderful new program. You will become part of our band family, make lifelong friends in all grades, and have the opportunity to participate in something unique and exciting. Performances will include pregame and halftime at home football games, parades, a few home basketball games, and more.

No prior experience is necessary! If you are interested in participating in this new performance group, please contact:

Ms. Cox at jeracox@readingschools.org or call/text at 513-535-4373

Great news! It‚Äôs now even easier to support Reading Band Boosters when you shop Amazon! AmazonSmile is now available in the Amazon Shopping app on iOS and Android mobile phones.

AmazonSmile customers can now support Reading Band Boosters Inc in the Amazon shopping app on iOS and Android mobile phones! Simply follow these instructions to turn on AmazonSmile and start generating donations:

- Open the Amazon Shopping app on your device
- Go into the main menu of the Amazon Shopping app and tap into 'Settings'
- Tap 'AmazonSmile' and follow the on-screen instructions to complete the process

post_text: It‚Äôs been a year of ‚Äúfirsts‚Äù ... and last night we had our first ever virtual Band Banquet via Zoom. 30+ kids from 7-12th grades logged on to chromebooks, laptops and cellphones to reconnect with their friends to celebrate the year of Marching and Pep Bands. Each band member received a special Band Banquet Porch Delivery that included balloons (to decorate), cookies (to eat), a paper plate award (to recognize them for something fun) and a gift from the band boosters (a T-shirt to commemorate 2020). We watched videos to celebrate Ronnie, our one and only Senior, and to celebrate our year from band camp through pep band (the videos are posted in separate posts for your viewing pleasure). post_text: Support the Reading Police Department ‚ÄúShop with a Cop‚Äù Program, which provides a fun filled evening for a number of children throughout Reading, while creating positive relationships with law enforcement. The Reading Police Department has been able to provide the experience for many families over the years and last year set a record of sponsoring 13 families! This is only possible because of the generous donations given by the staff of the Reading School District, the citizens and businesses of Reading, as well as the Officers and Staff of the Reading Police Department. Please help keep this amazing program going by donating to this year‚Äôs Shop with a Cop program. Checks can be made payable to Reading Police Department. You can make a donation at the Holiday Shoppers Fair on Saturday, December 7th from 9 am - 2 pm. There will also be a Door Prize Raffle, and all proceeds will be donated to Shop with a Cop.

If you have a student in Reading Community Schools (Pre-K to 12th grade), are an Alumni or a Reading Staff member, we‚Äôve got exciting news! Reading Band Boosters is taking orders for Class Of 2020-2034, Alumni and Staff shirts.

Shirts are available in royal, black or gray. Tshirts, long sleeve t-shirts, sweatshirt hoodies and hooded long sleeve t-shirts are available in Youth and Adult sizes.

Orders and payment are due by November 15th. Order Form is available to print online from Readingschools.org (link will be in comments). If you have any questions, please email: readingbandboosters@gmail.

This is a fundraiser for the Blue Devil Band - we appreciate your support!

Please share this post with family and friends.

Tag Day is this Saturday, October 12th. Reading Blue Devil Marching Band members will come door-to-door from 10 am- 2:00pm in small groups asking for donations from members of our community. ‚ÄúTag Day" is a longstanding tradition for marching bands throughout the country, and this marks our 4th annual Tag Day.

Your donations go toward the band‚Äôs general fund to help cover costs that are steadily growing with our growing band program!

Because of the generosity of the Reading Community at our various fundraisers over the last 5 years, we have been able to purchase 75 new uniforms. We will need to purchase a few more uniforms each year as we grow and need different sizes. We were also able to‚Ä¶

Reading Community City Schools
September 18, 2019 at 8:05 AM ¬∑

Building the Blue Devil Band...
Our band program continues to grow and we're always looking for new musicians! Beginning in 5th-grade, students are able to join the Blue Devil Band program. Yesterday, all of our 5th-grade students had the opportunity to try an instrument in music class.

If your child is interested in joining the band, learn more at a parent meeting being held in the RHS band room with Buddy Rogers music at 6:30 p.m. this Thursday night, September 19th. Please enter through the Middle School Entrance. Students are not required to attend this meeting.

#BlueDevilPride #BlueDevilBand

post_text:
DEADLINE TO PURCHASE IS FRIDAY 9/6 MIDNIGHT

BENGALS FOOTBALL SQUARES FUNDRAISER TO BENEFIT READING BAND BOOSTERS!

1) The cost of each square is $25 (16 chances to win)
2) You will receive a number (drawn randomly) for the Bengals score and also a number (drawn randomly) for the opponent's score. If your numbers match the ENDING numbers of the ENDING score of the Bengals game, you will win $75.

EXAMPLE: if you get a 0 for Bengals and a 1 for Opponent, and the ending game score was Bengals 10 - Opponent 21, your numbers match, so you win!

3) You will keep the same numbers for the ENTIRE regular football season.
4) There will be 16 WINNERS in total (1 every week that the Bengals play).
*There must be a minimum of 50 squares sold before we will start the fundraiser. If the 50 squares are not sold by the first BENGALS game (9/8), all of the money will be refunded.

To purchase a square, please email readingbandboosters@gmail.com.
Please Share.

And now it‚Äôs time to reveal the show to their families, so you ‚Äúgotta go‚Äù to the Parent Preview and Potluck Dinner Friday night!
‚è∞ Band Members should arrive at 6:15pm - they should wear their white ‚Äúdrill position‚Äù T-shirt they made in camp last week. When the clock strikes 6:30pm, the performance will start.
ü•ò After the performance, we will head inside for the potluck dinner and meeting where we will discuss important information for the marching season - if you haven‚Äôt already signed up to bring something, please see the signup genius link that was emailed.
üéº Band Fees are due, as well as payment for polo and show shirt orders. We will also have some spirit-wear for sale. T-shirts range in price from $5-$15 and hoodies $10-$25 while they last.
ü•Åüé∑üé∫ Can‚Äôt wait to see everyone and kick off the season!
